declare remote RPC-OPC-BROWSE(text, integer, text ) =(class text-list, integer, text)

g2:c.RULE.g2:a.TEXT: whenever the gsi-interface-status of any gsi-opc-interface INTFC receives a value and when the gsi-interface-status of INTFC /= 2 then conclude that the connection-status of INTFC = the symbol disconnected
whenever the gsi-interface-status of any gsi-opc-interface INTFC receives a value and when the gsi-interface-status of INTFC = 2 then start update-interface-object(INTFC)
whenever the connection-status of any gsi-opc-interface INTFC receives a value then start update-opc-interface-icon(INTFC)
initially for any gsi-opc-interface IO if the connection-status of IO exists then conclude that the connection-status of IO = the symbol disconnected

g2:c.PROCEDURE.g2:a.TEXT: update-all-opc-interface-icons() oio : class gsi-opc-interface; begin for oio = each gsi-opc-interface do if the gsi-interface-status of oio = 2 and the connection-status of oio exists then start update-interface-object(oio) end end
